an><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⋯</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Homotopic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"n\">path_ω_lift</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">map</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⋯</span><span class=\"o\">))</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>from <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Homotopy/Path.html#Path.Homotopic.map\">Path.Homotopic.map</a>. Is there a code for cancel the cast from both side of the homotopic?</p>",
